{
  "texts": [
    "So, Uber was able to make their own safety policies.",
    "A year before the incident, in 2017, Uber had changed their safety practices from requiring two humans in each test car (one driver and one to look out for and discuss hazards and to write up issues for the company to review), to only having one human in each self-driving car.",
    "This policy change had several impacts.",
    "Now, a single operator had to manage the complexities of each test drive.",
    "Additionally, there was no longer a conversational partner to share SA with and to prevent automation complacency."
  ]
}